    "image_with_text_X4xaaJ": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_rrjPrn": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Traceability",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_Yzw7yC": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>At Himalayan Cliff Honey, we are rooted in nature, people, and tradition. Every jar comes directly from native cliffside hives in Nepal, carefully harvested by experienced Gurung, Magar, and Chhetri honey hunters using centuries-old techniques.</p><p>Our cliff honey is collected once or twice a year, handled in small batches, and stored in certified units to preserve its natural enzymes, bioactive compounds, and delicate flavor with minimal processing.</p><p>Each jar includes a QR code that allows you to trace your honey back to its harvest region, season, and the beekeeper. The code also provides batch details and third-party quality testing information, ensuring full transparency from the cliff to your jar.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
